history.content:
I did set classes to allow time conflicts but there's some weirdness in the system that prevents it from working for some classes.

Email your SID and the class you want to get into to cs-enrollments@berkeley.edu and I will work to manually override the time conflict to enroll you. Do this by noon on Wednesday (2/13) to allow time for me to process your request before the add/drop deadline.

My decal instructors are trying to enroll me into the decal but they can't because the time conflicts with CS189 lecture.

I thought all CS classes allow time conflicts? Where can I go to resolve this time conflict so my instructors can enroll me?
history.subject: Time conflict with CS lecture
